news.title: Irregularities found in Raipur master plan to be probed: Jharkhand finance minister
news.para: Finance minister OP Choudhary acknowledged that complaints regarding the master plan were received and informed the House that a committee was constituted to investigate the matter.

news.title: Land circle rates in several districts of Uttar Pradesh set to be revised
news.para: A govt spokesperson said that the process has already been completed in 37 districts, but the work is now set to start in important districts as well.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC seizes properties of two builders over Rs 21 crore tax default
news.para: According to a BMC release, the civic body has started a crackdown on those defaulting on property tax payments by seizing and auctioning their properties.

news.title: Developers delaying SGNP flat transfer to displaced people: Maharashtra minister
news.para: In a written reply to a question by Shiv Sena (UBT) MLC Sachin Ahir, the state forest minister informed the legislative council that despite the government's efforts to rehabilitate people displaced due to removal of encroachments, developers have not transferred flats yet.

news.title: Four cement plants in Gurugram get GMDA notice for road damage
news.para: The enforcement action follows a site inspection by GMDA officials, revealing that the roads, constructed a year ago, suffered damage from heavy trucks and slurry spillage.

news.title: Gujarat assembly allocates Rs 30,325 crore for urban development for 2025-26
news.para: Speaking in the assembly, minister Rushikesh Patel said that a provision of Rs 450 crore has been made for infrastructural facilities in newly formed municipal corporations.

news.title: Telangana RERA slaps Rs 6 lakh penalty on builder for non-compliance
news.para: ​The order was issued following a complaint by Coconut Grove Flat Owners' Maintenance Mutually Aided Cooperative Society Limited, which alleged that the builder failed to deliver promised amenities and left significant portions of the project incomplete.

news.title: SC stays coercive action against Noida Sports City, CBI probe can go on
news.para: Last month, the Allahabad high court had ordered a CBI inquiry into an alleged nexus between builders and Noida Authority officials, where multiple benefits were purportedly granted to developers in violation of the scheme.

news.title: Macrotech Developers to buy Unichem's land parcel in Mumbai for Rs 279 crore
news.para: While the deal is yet to be inked and registered, Unichem’s board of directors have approved the plan to monetise this land parcel. The book value of this property in the company’s books of accounts is about Rs 2.18 crore.

news.title: Delhi Police issues guidelines for property owners, administrators regarding rental to foreigners
news.para: They must submit the required details of their foreign national tenants to the local police station for background verification, he said, adding that a register must be maintained in the prescribed Form 'B' format, which should be available for inspection by authorities upon request.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates must be sold as one unit, not by dividing assets: NCLT
news.para: ​NCLT has said 'Form G' published by the resolution professional of JAL inviting Expression of Interest (EOI) from prospective buyers "by giving two options at the threshold and the second option by splitting the business operations of JAL into multiple clusters being in violation of the provisions" of Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code (IBC).

news.title: Spanish hotel chain Melia buys properties for its workers as rents surge
news.para: "Due to the boom in short-term rentals for tourists, finding an apartment for the season has become an Odyssey," Escarrer said, adding that paying employees well is no longer enough to retain talent.

news.title: Rocket Companies to buy Redfin in $1.75 billion deal
news.para: Rocket's $12.50 per share offer equates to a near 115% premium to Redfin's Friday close. Redfin's shares rose about 80%, while Rocket's fell about 8% before the bell.

news.title: Construction cost for greenfield realty projects rises 2-4% in 2024: CBRE
news.para: In 2024, cement, steel, and aluminium costs dipped by 6-8 per cent, 3-5 per cent, and 0-2 per cent, respectively, on an annualised basis, while paint costs remained stable.

news.title: NCLT approves a resolution plan for Universal Buildwell Projects
news.para: The NCLT Bench, comprising Justice Ashok Kumar Bhardwaj and Justice Subrata Kumar Dash, approved the resolution plan.

news.title: Greenfield construction costs marginally rise by 2-4% in 2024
news.para: The report thoroughly examines the evolving market landscape, analyzing factors that influence construction cost trends across major real estate asset classes.

news.title: Assam cabinet approves setting up of industrial Park including a smart township in Hajo
news.para: Cabinet approved to pursue for Majuli and Sivasagar the status of UNESCO World Heritage Site under the appropriate categories by engaging experts

news.title: Renters turn to lottery in Spain's housing crisis
news.para: Like a growing number of Spaniards, the 30-year-old auxiliary nurse and her partner, Sergio Encinas, have found themselves priced out of the real estate market as rents have soared due to insufficient supply.

news.title: Nielsen leases 2.8 lakh sq ft across Bengaluru and Mumbai
news.para: The new offices has seating capacity for 1,500 employees each. The Mumbai office, leased from Oberoi Realty Limited, spans 1.5 lakh sq. ft., while the Bengaluru office, leased from Chalet Hotels Limited, covers 1.36 lakh sq.

news.title: Stamp duty evasion recovery fine after five years, not 10 years: Karnataka HC
news.para: The court, however, said there could be an exception from the five-year limit in cases of short payment on account of fraud, collusion or wilful misstatement.
